Female: Brachypterous, sometimes macropterous; length 3.9–4.9. COLORATION: Similar to that of male, but hemelytra uniformly dark brown to black, often with pale brown or yellowish stripe or spot along claval suture. SURFACE AND VESTITURE: Body 2.5–3.4× as long as width of pronotum. Head : 1.2–1.3× as wide as high; vertex 2.2–2.6× as wide as eye; antennal segment II 0.9–1.2× as long as basal width of pronotum, 1.0–1.3× as long as width of head. Thorax : Pronotum 1.7–2.5× as wide as long and 1.0–1.3× as wide as head; length of hemelytra in brachypterous specimens ranging from reaching abdominal tergum VII to covering entire abdomen, typically reaching abdominal tergum VII, cuneus of brachypterous specimens slightly delimited, claval commissure as long as inner claval margin, posterior and lateral margins of hemelytra rounded or posterior margin sometimes truncate. GENITALIA: Dorsal labiate plate with comparatively large, apically pointed sclerotized rings, medial sclerites curved and wide, apically tapering, twisted at extreme base, of approximately same length and width as sclerotized ring (fig. 17); posterior wall of bursa copulatrix with trapeziform sclerite uniformly sclerotized, incision on the anterior margin narrow and not reaching middle of sclerite, anterior angles of this sclerite somewhat dentate, posterior margin without sclerites (as in fig. 18,
bivittatus
); vulva with curved sclerites forming a circle (as in fig. 19,
O. styx
).
